<TITLE> Books should be easily available: CA </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 15 (bdnews24.com)  Chief adviser Fakhruddin Ahmed has asked writers and researchers to improve the quality of books and said books should be made easily available to readers. " Books should be easily available to increase reading habit," he said after launching Dhaka International Book Fair on Monday at Dhaka University. "There must be a cordial relation among publishers, writers and readers for the improvement of books." The government also has a role to play in facilitating better publications, added the chief adviser. He suggested such fairs held in other cities. "Let books be eternal partners for peaceful existence." Presided over by culture secretary Sharful Alam, culture adviser Rasheda K Chowdhury, president of the Biswa Sahitya Kendra Abdullah Abu Sayeed, director of the National Library Mahmudur Rahman also spoke at the launch. The Dhaka Book Fair launched in 1995 has emerged as the first Dhaka International Book Fair this year. The slogan this year is Books for a peaceful world. The fair, organised with the assistance of the ministry of culture, has 145 local and 13 foreign stalls and it will run through to Dec. 30. On Sunday, Alam, the culture secretary, said there will be a 25 percent discount on all books to encourage visitors to buy them. "Publisher with the highest number of books and sellers of most books will be awarded." The fair will be open to all from 11am to 8pm every day with the closing time extended to 8:30pm on weekends. The entry fee is Tk 5. b
